1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:01,760
Here, please have some.

2
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:03,560
Thank you.

3
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:16,840
The truth is, Kono Mizuki...

4
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,200
has a younger brother.

5
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:25,080
When Mizuki was in middle school,
his brother was in elementary school.

6
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:28,360
His name was Kono Hazuki.

7
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:30,240
A younger brother...

8
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,240
They lost their mother when they were young.

9
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:37,240
It was always just Mizuki, me,

10
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:39,400
and Hazuki living together.

11
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:43,360
Since I was always busy with work,

12
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:47,320
Mizuki practically raised his brother like a parent.

13
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,720
But then, that accident happened...

14
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:04,760
Mizuki was going through a rebellious phase back then.

15
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:07,920
He was out late with his friends.

16
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:10,680
And as a result,

17
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:13,240
he missed the time

18
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,000
he was supposed to pick Hazuki up from cram school.

19
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,880
Because his brother

20
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:23,760
never showed up,

21
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:29,520
I heard he started walking home alone.

22
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:33,600
And on the way...

23
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,240
he was in an accident.

24
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,140
That's horrible...

25
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:44,800
Of course, it wasn't Mizuki's fault.

26
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:48,160
As his father,

27
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:51,280
I failed to look after them properly.

28
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,120
The responsibility lies with me.

29
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,600
But Mizuki...

30
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,760
he doesn't see it that way.

31
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,760
Ever since then,
Mizuki has...

32
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,840
always

33
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,880
been blaming himself.

34
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,840
However,

35
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,160
after I remarried your mother,

36
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,440
and he met you,

37
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:38,760
he seemed to brighten up a bit.

38
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,880
Perhaps it's because

39
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:46,040
you remind him so much of Hazuki.

40
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,080
It's like he gained a younger brother again.

41
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:52,640
He must be very happy about that.

42
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:58,320
I'm sorry.

43
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:01,640
I shouldn't have dropped all this on you. It's a lot to take in, isn't it?

44
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,200
It is...

45
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:09,300
It's incredibly heavy...

46
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,500
If you don't mind,

47
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:33,220
I hope you two can continue to get along well.

48
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:34,220
It would mean a lot to me.

49
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,440
Kono Mizuki...

50
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:51,880
What is it?

51
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:56,480
I heard you used to have a younger brother?

52
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,920
Did my dad tell you?

53
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:10,920
It's all my fault.

54
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,080
Hazuki died because of me.

55
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,960
Whenever I feel happy,

56
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:21,120
or whenever I find myself laughing,

57
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,080
my heart just aches.

58
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,480
Is that why you said you wouldn't come to the school festival?

59
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:34,580
Yeah.

60
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,480
What could I possibly say

61
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,480
to him now...?
